sentences: Manus Lunny (born 1962) is an Irish producer and multi-instrumentalist from County Donegal, Ireland, best known as a member of Celtic supergroup Capercaillie.
Donegal for many years now, close to where his mother was born in Ranafast.
He toured widely with Barry Moore (now Luka Bloom) as a teenager.
After decades of gigging and recording, Lunny finally gotten around to making a CD of his own compositions titled The Glenveagh Suite.
Lunny had a gathering on 29 September 2018 (9pm) in Leo's Tavern in Meenaleck to mark the launch and also to play music for the occasion.
